<subSubSection pageId="393" pageNumber="394" type="note">
<paragraph pageId="393" pageNumber="394">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="393" pageNumber="394">
Hayward (1901: 158) listed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chaudoir" authorityYear="1868" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="393" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilatei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="393" pageNumber="394">Bembidion pilatei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Chaudoir as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="LeConte" baseAuthorityYear="1847" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="393" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="constrictum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="393" pageNumber="394">Bembidion constrictum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
LeConte but Lindroth (1963b: 373) regarded the two forms as distinct species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
